 {"id":"bd-1zrz","title":"Renderer tests: Buffer access and management","description":"# Renderer Buffer Access Tests

## Scope
Test buffer access patterns and double-buffering mechanics.

## Functions to Test
1. `size()` - Dimension queries
2. `buffer()` - Back buffer mutable access
3. `buffer_with_pool()` - Buffer + grapheme pool combined access
4. `front_buffer()` - Front buffer immutable access

## Test Cases

### size()
- [ ] Returns correct width and height after construction
- [ ] Returns correct size after resize()
- [ ] Consistent with buffer dimensions

### buffer()
- [ ] Returns mutable reference to back buffer
- [ ] Modifications persist across calls
- [ ] Drawing operations work correctly
- [ ] Multiple mutable borrows prevented (compile-time)

### buffer_with_pool()
- [ ] Returns buffer and pool together
- [ ] Pool is usable for grapheme operations
- [ ] Graphemes allocated in pool appear in buffer

### front_buffer()
- [ ] Returns immutable reference
- [ ] Reflects state from last present()
